{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874940383,"sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","part":{"id":"prt_d7a63c7b1001S2hgbTsGSJY971","messageID":"msg_d7a63bf00001bCL2y6yh9XrJ3G","sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_7de57b57fddd481a9e0a6d69","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark to understand:\n1. Project structure and what it does\n2. Any existing Dockerfile(s) - find and read them\n3. Any existing docker-related configuration (docker-compose.yml, .dockerignore, etc.)\n4. Any existing proposal.md files to understand the format/convention used\n5. Any specs related to \"docker\" module\n6. The package.json or equivalent to understand the tech stack\n\nReturn: full content of any Dockerfile found, docker-compose.yml, .dockerignore, and any existing proposal.md format examples. Also describe what the project does and its tech stack.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2859c2290ffesxuSrK2bJFJ4Yl (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is a comprehensive report of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Project Overview: What It Does\n\nThis project is **SDD-TEE v5.1 (Specification-Driven Development -- Token Efficiency Evaluation)**. It is a benchmark framework that measures and quantifies the **token consumption** of AI coding assistants when developing real open-source projects using a Specification-Driven Development (SDD) workflow.\n\nThe project uses the **agentcube** open-source project (https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube) as the target codebase. Agentcube itself is a **Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents** -- it provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic through session-aware proxies, and manages sandbox lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\nThe benchmark:\n- Decomposes agentcube into **43 granular Architectural Requirements (ARs)**\n- Each AR goes through a full SDD pipeline: `/opsx:new` -> `/opsx:ff` -> `/opsx:apply` -> `/opsx:verify` -> `/opsx:archive`\n- Quantifies token consumption across **8 stages (ST-0~ST-7) x 5 dimensions**\n- Supports multiple CLI tools (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, Cursor CLI, OpenCode CLI) and multiple LLM models\n- Uses **LiteLLM Proxy** as the authoritative token data source (port 4000)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Dockerfile(s) -- FINDINGS\n\n**No Dockerfiles exist in this benchmark project itself.** The glob search for `**/Dockerfile*` returned no results.\n\nHowever, the **specs/deployment/design.md** (lines 157-178) contains **detailed specifications** for three Dockerfiles that should exist in the target agentcube repository:\n\n### Specified Dockerfile 1: `docker/Dockerfile` (Workload Manager)\n```dockerfile\n# Build stage\nFROM golang:1.24.9-alpine AS builder\nWORKDIR /workspace\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\nCOPY cmd/ cmd/\nCOPY pkg/ pkg/\nRUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n    CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} \\\n    go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n\n# Runtime stage\nFROM alpine:3.19\nRUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY --from=builder /workspace/workloadmanager /app/workloadmanager\nRUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver\nUSER apiserver\nEXPOSE 8080\nENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]\nCMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n```\n\n### Specified Dockerfile 2: `docker/Dockerfile.router` (Router)\nSame multi-stage pattern as workloadmanager, plus:\n- `COPY client-go/ client-go/` in builder stage\n- Output binary: `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router`\n- Runtime user: `router` UID 1000\n- `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`\n\n### Specified Dockerfile 3: `docker/Dockerfile.picod` (PicoD)\n```dockerfile\n# Build stage\nFROM golang:1.24.4 AS builder\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\nCOPY . .\nRUN CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o picod ./cmd/picod\n\n# Runtime stage\nFROM ubuntu:24.04\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y python3\nWORKDIR /root/\nCOPY --from=builder /app/picod ./picod\n# Runs as root (chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions)\nENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]\n```\n\n### Specified Dockerfile 4: `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` (from PLAN.md, lines 387-411)\n```dockerfile\nFROM ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Install uv and dependencies\nRUN uv venv\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN uv pip install -r requirements.txt\n\n# Vendor agentcube SDK from monorepo\nCOPY sdk-python/agentcube ./agentcube/\n\n# Copy application\nCOPY pcap_analyzer.py ./\n\nENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"\nEXPOSE 8000\n\nCMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Docker-Related Configuration\n\n**No docker-compose.yml or .dockerignore files exist** in this project. Glob searches for both returned no results.\n\nThe `.gitignore` file at `/home/dsj/benchmark/.gitignore` has no Docker-specific entries. It excludes:\n- `workspaces/` (runtime workspaces)\n- `results/litellm_usage.db`\n- Standard Python/Node/IDE artifacts\n\nThe **specs/deployment/design.md** (lines 187-235) specifies Makefile Docker targets that should exist in the agentcube repo:\n- `docker-build`, `docker-buildx`, `docker-buildx-push`, `docker-push`, `kind-load`\n- Same pattern for `-router` and `-picod` variants\n- Uses `CONTAINER_TOOL=docker` variable\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing proposal.md Format\n\nThere is **one existing proposal.md** at `/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md`. This is a concrete example for **AR-008 -- Sandbox GC Garbage Collection Mechanism**.\n\nThe format convention is:\n\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX — <Feature Name>\n\n## Purpose\n<One paragraph describing what and why>\n\n## Scope\n### In scope\n| Item | Detail |\n(out-of-scope items)\n\n## Design\n### File layout\n| File | Role |\n\n### Constants / GVR definitions / Structs / Methods\n(Go code blocks with full implementations)\n\n### Algorithm descriptions (gcLoop, tick, deleteSandbox, etc.)\n\n## Impact analysis\n### Files created / Files modified / Dependencies / Downstream consumers\n### Breaking change risk / Performance characteristics / Edge cases\n\n## Alternatives considered\n(Numbered alternatives with \"Rejected because\" or \"Deferred because\" rationale)\n\n## Integration with Server\n(Startup/shutdown sequence code)\n\n## Verification\n(Bash commands to test)\n\n## Testing strategy\n(Numbered unit test descriptions + test helper code)\n```\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Uses **normative language** (SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional)\n- Includes **full Go code** for structs, constructors, methods, and algorithms\n- Has explicit **alternatives considered** section with rejection rationale\n- Includes **impact analysis** with file-level detail\n- Has **testing strategy** with specific test cases\n\n---\n\n## 5. Docker-Related Specs\n\nDocker-related specifications are found in:\n\n| File | Content |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/spec.md` | Lines 77-83: Docker image requirements (3 Dockerfiles for Workload Manager, Router, PicoD) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md` | Lines 157-178: Full Dockerfile specifications (multi-stage builds, base images, users, ports) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md` | Lines 187-235: Makefile Docker targets |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/ci-cd/spec.md` | Lines 9-14, 86: CI Docker build and push requirements |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/ci-cd/design.md` | Lines 9, 18, 55-57, 174-179: CI/CD Docker workflow details |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/spec.md` | Lines 23, 41-51, 59, 135-149: CLI Docker integration (DockerService, build_image, push_image) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/design.md` | Lines 22, 63, 149-152, 207, 379: DockerService class design |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/integrations/design.md` | Lines 119, 197-209: PCAP analyzer Dockerfile highlights |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Tech Stack\n\n### Benchmark Framework (this project):\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language | Python 3 |\n| Dependencies | pyyaml>=6.0, litellm>=1.50.0, matplotlib>=3.7.0, rich>=13.0.0 |\n| CLI tooling | Makefile, bash scripts |\n| Token tracking | LiteLLM Proxy (port 4000), JSONL logs |\n| Spec tooling | OpenSpec OPSX CLI (`@fission-ai/openspec`) |\n\n### Target Project (agentcube):\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python >=3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n| Auth | JWT RS256, K8s TokenReview |\n| Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n| Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n| Container base images | golang:1.24.9-alpine, alpine:3.19, ubuntu:24.04, python3.12-bookworm-slim |\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Absolute File Paths\n\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| Existing proposal.md | `/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md` |\n| PROPOSAL.md (benchmark design doc) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/PROPOSAL.md` |\n| PLAN.md (implementation plan) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md` |\n| Deployment spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/spec.md` |\n| Deployment design | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md` |\n| CI/CD spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/ci-cd/spec.md` |\n| CI/CD design | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/ci-cd/design.md` |\n| CLI toolkit spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/spec.md` |\n| CLI toolkit design | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/design.md` |\n| Project context | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/project.md` |\n| Requirements | `/home/dsj/benchmark/requirements.txt` |\n| Makefile | `/home/dsj/benchmark/Makefile` |\n| .gitignore | `/home/dsj/benchmark/.gitignore` |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2859c2290ffesxuSrK2bJFJ4Yl","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project","time":{"start":1775874858349,"end":1775874940380}}}}
