{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874942902,"sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6525fe001Q92wntIDMx9noC","messageID":"msg_d7a651e2d0019nYYpU339630uK","sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_f8fedca3d96546b5901ff5ea","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement a time-based garbage collection mechanism in `pkg/workloadmanager` to automatically clean up idle and expired sandboxes. The GarbageCollector periodically scans the store for sandboxes that exceed idle timeout or max session duration thresholds, then deletes them via Kubernetes API and removes their metadata from the store. This ensures resource efficiency and prevents sandbox leakage in production environments.\n6: \n7: ## Scope\n8: \n9: ### In scope\n10: \n11: | Item | Detail |\n12: |------|--------|\n13: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n14: | **Component** | `GarbageCollector` struct with lifecycle management |\n15: | **GVRs managed** | `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/Sandbox`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/SandboxClaim` |\n16: | **Cleanup triggers** | Idle timeout (no activity for 15m), Max session duration exceeded (8h) |\n17: | **Store operations** | `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` |\n18: | **Audit logging** | klog-based cleanup audit entries with success/failure status |\n19: | **Default timing** | GC interval: 15s, Batch size: 16, Single tick timeout: 2m |\n20: \n21: ### Out of scope\n22: \n23: - Idle timeout configuration per `AgentRuntime` CR (uses global `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout`)\n24: - `agentd` reconciler for sandbox-side idle tracking (separate AR)\n25: - Custom cleanup policies or hooks\n26: - Resource quota enforcement\n27: - Metrics/monitoring integration\n28: \n29: ## Design\n30: \n31: ### File layout\n32: \n33: | File | Role |\n34: |------|------|\n35: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | `GarbageCollector` struct, constructor, lifecycle methods, cleanup logic |\n36: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | Unit tests for GC initialization, loop behavior, cleanup scenarios |\n37: \n38: ### Constants\n39: \n40: ```go\n41: const (\n42:     DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n43:     DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n44:     GCSingleTickTimeout       = 2 * time.Minute\n45:     DeleteTimeout             = 30 * time.Second\n46: )\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### GVR definitions\n50: \n51: ```go\n52: var (\n53:     SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n54:         Group:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n55:         Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n56:         Resource: \"sandboxes\",\n57:     }\n58: \n59:     SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n60:         Group:    \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\",\n61:         Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n62:         Resource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n63:     }\n64: )\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ### GarbageCollector struct\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: type GarbageCollector struct {\n71:     dynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n72:     storeClient   store.Store\n73:     interval      time.Duration\n74:     ctx           context.Context\n75:     cancel        context.CancelFunc\n76: }\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Constructor\n80: \n81: ```go\n82: func NewGarbageCollector(\n83:     dynamicClient dynamic.Interface,\n84:     storeClient store.Store,\n85:     interval time.Duration,\n86: ) *GarbageCollector {\n87:     ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n88:     return &GarbageCollector{\n89:         dynamicClient: dynamicClient,\n90:         storeClient:   storeClient,\n91:         interval:      interval,\n92:         ctx:           ctx,\n93:         cancel:        cancel,\n94:     }\n95: }\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### Lifecycle methods\n99: \n100: **Start**: launches `gcLoop` in background goroutine\n101: \n102: ```go\n103: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Start() {\n104:     go gc.gcLoop()\n105: }\n106: ```\n107: \n108: **Stop**: cancels context to terminate loop\n109: \n110: ```go\n111: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Stop() {\n112:     gc.cancel()\n113: }\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ### gcLoop algorithm\n117: \n118: ```go\n119: func (gc *GarbageCollector) gcLoop() {\n120:     ticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)\n121:     defer ticker.Stop()\n122: \n123:     klog.Info(\"GarbageCollector started\")\n124: \n125:     for {\n126:         select {\n127:         case <-gc.ctx.Done():\n128:             klog.Info(\"GarbageCollector stopped\")\n129:             return\n130:         case <-ticker.C:\n131:             gc.tick()\n132:         }\n133:     }\n134: }\n135: ```\n136: \n137: ### tick cleanup logic\n138: \n139: ```go\n140: func (gc *GarbageCollector) tick() {\n141:     tickCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(gc.ctx, GCSingleTickTimeout)\n142:     defer cancel()\n143: \n144:     now := time.Now()\n145:     idleThreshold := now.Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout)\n146:     expiredThreshold := now\n147: \n148:     // Clean up idle sandboxes\n149:     idleSandboxes, err := gc.storeClient.ListInactiveSandboxes(tickCtx, idleThreshold, 16)\n150:     if err != nil {\n151:         klog.Errorf(\"Failed to list inactive sandboxes: %v\", err)\n152:     } else {\n153:         for _, sandbox := range idleSandboxes {\n154:             gc.deleteSandbox(tickCtx, sandbox, wmTypes.CleanupReasonIdleTimeout)\n155:         }\n156:     }\n157: \n158:     // Clean up expired sandboxes\n159:     expiredSandboxes, err := gc.storeClient.ListExpiredSandboxes(tickCtx, expiredThreshold, 16)\n160:     if err != nil {\n161:         klog.Errorf(\"Failed to list expired sandboxes: %v\", err)\n162:     } else {\n163:         for _, sandbox := range expiredSandboxes {\n164:             gc.deleteSandbox(tickCtx, sandbox, wmTypes.CleanupReasonExpired)\n165:         }\n166:     }\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### deleteSandbox algorithm\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: func (gc *GarbageCollector) deleteSandbox(\n174:     ctx context.Context,\n175:     sandbox *types.SandboxInfo,\n176:     reason wmTypes.SandboxCleanupReason,\n177: ) {\n178:     auditEntry := &wmTypes.CleanupAuditEntry{\n179:         SessionID: sandbox.SessionID,\n180:         SandboxID: sandbox.SandboxID,\n181:         Namespace: sandbox.SandboxNamespace,\n182:         Reason:    reason,\n183:         DeletedAt: time.Now(),\n184:     }\n185: \n186:     gvr := SandboxGVR\n187:     if sandbox.Kind == \"SandboxClaim\" {\n188:         gvr = SandboxClaimGVR\n189:     }\n190: \n191:     deleteCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, DeleteTimeout)\n192:     defer cancel()\n193: \n194:     err := gc.dynamicClient.Resource(gvr).\n195:         Namespace(sandbox.SandboxNamespace).\n196:         Delete(deleteCtx, sandbox.SandboxID, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n197: \n198:     if err != nil && !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n199:         auditEntry.ErrorMessage = err.Error()\n200:         auditEntry.Success = false\n201:         klog.Errorf(\"Failed to delete sandbox %s/%s: %v\", sandbox.SandboxNamespace, sandbox.SandboxID, err)\n202:     } else {\n203:         if err := gc.storeClient.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sandbox.SessionID); err != nil {\n204:             klog.Warningf(\"Failed to delete sandbox %s from store: %v\", sandbox.SessionID, err)\n205:         }\n206:         auditEntry.Success = true\n207:         klog.Infof(\"Deleted sandbox %s/%s (reason: %s)\", sandbox.SandboxNamespace, sandbox.SandboxID, reason)\n208:     }\n209: \n210:     gc.recordAudit(auditEntry)\n211: }\n212: ```\n213: \n214: ### Audit logging\n215: \n216: ```go\n217: func (gc *GarbageCollector) recordAudit(entry *wmTypes.CleanupAuditEntry) {\n218:     klog.Infof(\"Cleanup audit: sessionId=%s sandboxId=%s namespace=%s reason=%s success=%v deletedAt=%s\",\n219:         entry.SessionID, entry.SandboxID, entry.Namespace, entry.Reason, entry.Success, entry.DeletedAt.Format(time.RFC3339))\n220:     if entry.ErrorMessage != \"\" {\n221:         klog.Infof(\"Cleanup audit error: %s\", entry.ErrorMessage)\n222:     }\n223: }\n224: ```\n225: \n226: ### CleanupAuditEntry type (`pkg/workloadmanager/types`)\n227: \n228: ```go\n229: type SandboxCleanupReason string\n230: \n231: const (\n232:     CleanupReasonIdleTimeout SandboxCleanupReason = \"IdleTimeout\"\n233:     CleanupReasonExpired     SandboxCleanupReason = \"Expired\"\n234: )\n235: \n236: type CleanupAuditEntry struct {\n237:     SessionID   string\n238:     SandboxID   string\n239:     Namespace   string\n240:     Reason      SandboxCleanupReason\n241:     DeletedAt   time.Time\n242:     Success     bool\n243:     ErrorMessage string\n244: }\n245: ```\n246: \n247: ## Impact analysis\n248: \n249: ### Files created\n250: \n251: | File | Lines (est.) |\n252: |------|-------------|\n253: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | ~150 |\n254: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types/cleanup.go` | ~30 |\n255: \n256: ### Files modified\n257: \n258: | File | Change |\n259: |------|--------|\n260: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server/server.go` | Add GC initialization and start in startup sequence |\n261: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Export `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout`, `DefaultSandboxTTL` constants |\n262: \n263: ### Dependencies\n264: \n265: | Dependency | Usage |\n266: |------------|-------|\n267: | `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Delete Sandbox/SandboxClaim resources |\n268: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | Handle `IsNotFound` gracefully |\n269: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured audit logging |\n270: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | List and delete sandbox metadata |\n271: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` struct |\n272: \n273: ### Downstream consumers\n274: \n275: | Consumer | Dependency |\n276: |----------|-----------|\n277: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Calls `NewGarbageCollector` and `Start()` |\n278: | `pkg/store` | Must implement `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `ListExpiredSandboxes` |\n279: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types` | Imports `CleanupAuditEntry`, `SandboxCleanupReason` |\n280: \n281: ### Breaking change risk\n282: \n283: **Low**: This is a new background service. No existing APIs or behaviors are modified. The GC operates transparently on existing sandbox resources.\n284: \n285: ### Performance characteristics\n286: \n287: - **GC interval**: 15s (configurable via constructor)\n288: - **Batch size**: 16 sandboxes per tick (prevents API throttling)\n289: - **Single tick timeout**: 2m (prevents runaway goroutines)\n290: - **Delete timeout**: 30s per sandbox (prevents hanging on slow deletes)\n291: - **Store queries**: 2x per tick (idle list + expired list)\n292: \n293: ### Edge cases handled\n294: \n295: 1. **Store unavailable**: Error logged, tick completes silently, retries next interval\n296: 2. **Sandbox already deleted**: `IsNotFound` treated as success\n297: 3. **Delete fails**: Error logged, sandbox remains in store, will be retried next tick\n298: 4. **Context cancelled during delete**: Timeout context ensures cleanup completes or aborts cleanly\n299: 5. **Kind mismatch**: GVR selected dynamically based on `sandbox.Kind` field\n300: \n301: ## Alternatives considered\n302: \n303: ### 1. Use controller-runtime manager with Reconciler pattern\n304: \n305: **Approach**: Implement GC as a controller-runtime reconciler that watches Sandbox resources and triggers cleanup based on annotation timestamps.\n306: \n307: **Rejected because**: \n308: - Workload Manager is a Gin-based HTTP service, not a controller-runtime application\n309: - Adding controller-runtime would introduce significant complexity and runtime overhead\n310: - Time-based cleanup is more efficiently handled by polling than by reconciler requeue patterns\n311: - Current architecture already has a dedicated `agentd` reconciler for sandbox-side idle tracking\n312: \n313: ### 2. Event-driven cleanup via Kubernetes TTL controller\n314: \n315: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes built-in TTL (`metadata.deletionTimestamp` + `ttlSecondsAfterFinish`) to auto-delete expired sandboxes.\n316: \n317: **Rejected because**:\n318: - TTL only handles max duration, not idle timeout (requires last-activity tracking)\n319: - Would require changes to sandbox controller to set deletion timestamps\n320: - Less flexible for custom cleanup logic (audit logging, store cleanup)\n321: - Doesn't integrate with application-level session metadata in Redis store\n322: \n323: ### 3. Per-session goroutine with `time.AfterFunc`\n324: \n325: **Approach**: When creating a sandbox, spawn a goroutine with `time.AfterFunc(idleTimeout, cleanupCallback)` that fires when idle.\n326: \n327: **Rejected because**:\n328: - Memory leak risk: thousands of sessions = thousands of goroutines\n329: - Difficult to track/update idle timeout when activity occurs\n330: - No centralized visibility into cleanup state\n331: - Harder to test and debug than centralized polling loop\n332: \n333: ### 4. External cron job / Kubernetes CronJob\n334: \n335: **Approach**: Run cleanup as an external scheduled job that calls workload-manager API or directly deletes resources.\n336: \n337: **Rejected because**:\n338: - Adds operational complexity (separate deployment, RBAC, monitoring)\n339: - Tighter integration with store requires direct DB access or extra API endpoints\n340: - Less responsive than in-process GC (cron interval typically minutes, not seconds)\n341: - Audit logging and error handling more complex across process boundaries\n342: \n343: ### 5. Configurable GC interval and batch size\n344: \n345: **Approach**: Expose `interval` and `batchSize` as CLI flags or config options.\n346: \n347: **Deferred because**: Current hardcoded defaults (15s interval, 16 batch) are sufficient for initial deployment. Can be made configurable if production monitoring shows need for tuning.\n348: \n349: ## Integration with Server\n350: \n351: ### Server struct addition\n352: \n353: ```go\n354: type Server struct {\n355:     // ... existing fields ...\n356:     garbageCollector *GarbageCollector\n357: }\n358: ```\n359: \n360: ### Startup sequence in `Run()` method\n361: \n362: ```go\n363: // After storeClient and k8sClient initialization\n364: gc := NewGarbageCollector(k8sClient.dynamicClient, storeClient, 15*time.Second)\n365: s.garbageCollector = gc\n366: gc.Start()\n367: ```\n368: \n369: ### Shutdown sequence\n370: \n371: ```go\n372: // In graceful shutdown\n373: if s.garbageCollector != nil {\n374:     s.garbageCollector.Stop()\n375: }\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ## Verification\n379: \n380: ```bash\n381: # Run unit tests\n382: go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector\n383: \n384: # Verify no generated files need updating\n385: make gen-check\n386: \n387: # Integration test (manual)\n388: # 1. Create sandbox via API\n389: # 2. Wait for idle timeout (15m)\n390: # 3. Verify sandbox deleted and audit log entry present\n391: ```\n392: \n393: ## Testing strategy\n394: \n395: ### Unit tests (`garbage_collector_test.go`)\n396: \n397: 1. **TestNewGarbageCollector**: Verify constructor initializes all fields correctly\n398: 2. **TestGarbageCollector_StartStop**: Verify goroutine lifecycle (start, stop, no panic)\n399: 3. **TestGarbageCollector_tick_IdleCleanup**: Mock store returns idle sandbox, verify delete called\n400: 4. **TestGarbageCollector_tick_ExpiredCleanup**: Mock store returns expired sandbox, verify delete called\n401: 5. **TestGarbageCollector_deleteSandbox_NotFound**: Verify `IsNotFound` treated as success\n402: 6. **TestGarbageCollector_deleteSandbox_StoreError**: Verify error logged but audit recorded\n403: 7. **TestGarbageCollector_tick_ContextTimeout**: Verify tick respects context timeout\n404: 8. **TestGarbageCollector_tick_StoreError**: Verify error logged, loop continues\n405: \n406: ### Test helpers\n407: \n408: ```go\n409: func newFakeStore() *fakeStore {\n410:     return &fakeStore{\n411:         inactiveSandboxes: []*types.SandboxInfo{},\n412:         expiredSandboxes:  []*types.SandboxInfo{},\n413:     }\n414: }\n415: \n416: func newFakeDynamicClient() *fakeDynamicClient {\n417:     return &fakeDynamicClient{\n418:         deletedResources: make(map[string]sets.Void),\n419:     }\n420: }\n421: ```\n\n(End of file - total 421 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement a time-based garbage collection mechanism in `pkg/workloadmanager` to automatically clean up idle and expired sandboxes. The GarbageCollector periodically scans the store for sandboxes that exceed idle timeout or max session duration thresholds, then deletes them via Kubernetes API and removes their metadata from the store. This ensures resource efficiency and prevents sandbox leakage in production environments.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| **Component** | `GarbageCollector` struct with lifecycle management |\n| **GVRs managed** | `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/Sandbox`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/SandboxClaim` |\n| **Cleanup triggers** | Idle timeout (no activity for 15m), Max session duration exceeded (8h) |\n| **Store operations** | `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` |\n| **Audit logging** | klog-based cleanup audit entries with success/failure status |\n| **Default timing** | GC interval: 15s, Batch size: 16, Single tick timeout: 2m |\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"proposal.md","time":{"start":1775874942893,"end":1775874942901}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874943479,"sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","part":{"id":"prt_d7a65283e001ra9m7Mtn4wPqSo","messageID":"msg_d7a651e2d0019nYYpU339630uK","sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5e8f291bd9b2435b9cead63e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775874943471,"end":1775874943477}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874944124,"sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","part":{"id":"prt_d7a652ac4001guqVVg0wsJb3re","messageID":"msg_d7a651e2d0019nYYpU339630uK","sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0d1fb2672803477cb3372d80","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Design\n2: \n3: Source tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n4: \n5: ## Chart.yaml\n6: \n7: | Field | Value |\n8: |--------|--------|\n9: | `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n10: | `name` | `agentcube` |\n11: | `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n12: | `version` | `0.1.0` |\n13: | `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n14: \n15: ## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n16: \n17: | Path | Type | Default |\n18: |------|------|---------|\n19: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n20: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n21: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n22: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` |\n23: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` |\n24: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` |\n25: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` |\n26: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n27: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n28: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n29: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n30: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` |\n31: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n32: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n33: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n34: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n35: | `router.config` | object | `{}` |\n36: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n37: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` |\n38: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` |\n39: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` |\n40: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` |\n41: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n42: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n43: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n44: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n45: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n46: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n47: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n48: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n49: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n50: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` |\n51: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` |\n52: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` |\n53: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n54: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n55: \n56: Comments in `values.yaml` state Redis settings “must be provided by the user during installation”; defaults are still empty strings.\n57: \n58: ## Template files (`manifests/charts/base/templates/`)\n59: \n60: ### `workloadmanager.yaml`\n61: \n62: | Kind | Name | Namespace | Notes |\n63: |------|------|-----------|--------|\n64: | `Deployment` | `workloadmanager` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` | `replicas`: `workloadmanager.replicas`; `serviceAccountName`: `workloadmanager`; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `workloadmanager`; image `repository:tag`; `imagePullPolicy`; port `http` → `workloadmanager.service.port`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef `metadata.namespace`), `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_ADDR`, plus `workloadmanager.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=` (empty); **resources**: from values; **liveness/readiness**: HTTP GET `/health` on service port, delays 10s/10s and 5s/5s |\n65: | `Service` | `workloadmanager` | release ns | `type`: `workloadmanager.service.type`; port & `targetPort`: `workloadmanager.service.port`; selector `app: workloadmanager` |\n66: \n67: ### `agentcube-router.yaml`\n68: \n69: | Kind | Name | Notes |\n70: |------|------|--------|\n71: | `Deployment` | `agentcube-router` | `replicas`: `router.replicas`; **conditional** `serviceAccountName` if `router.serviceAccountName` non-empty; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `agentcube-router`; image from `router.image`; container port `router.service.targetPort`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, plus `router.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`; **resources** from values; **liveness** `/health/live`, **readiness** `/health/ready` on targetPort, 1s initial, 2s period |\n72: | `Service` | `agentcube-router` | `type` `router.service.type`; `port` `router.service.port`, `targetPort` `router.service.targetPort`; selector `app: agentcube-router` |\n73: \n74: ### `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n75: \n76: | Kind | Name | Scope | Notes |\n77: |------|------|-------|--------|\n78: | `ServiceAccount` | `workloadmanager` | release namespace | — |\n79: | `ClusterRole` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | rules below |\n80: | `ClusterRoleBinding` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | binds `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` to `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in release namespace |\n81: \n82: ### `rbac-router.yaml`\n83: \n84: Rendered **only if** `router.rbac.create` is true.\n85: \n86: | Kind | Name pattern | Notes |\n87: |------|--------------|--------|\n88: | `ServiceAccount` | `{{ router.serviceAccountName \\| default \"agentcube-router\" }}` | release namespace |\n89: | `Role` | same as SA name | rules: `secrets` in `\"\"` apiGroup, full verb set `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n90: | `RoleBinding` | same | subject: SA above; `Role` ref same name |\n91: \n92: ### `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n93: \n94: Rendered **only if** `volcano.scheduler.enabled`.\n95: \n96: Creates (in order in file): `ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler`; `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` with key `agent-scheduler.conf` (actions `allocate`, tiers predicates/nodeorder); `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` (large rule set — see RBAC section); `ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role`; `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` (port 8080 metrics annotations); `Deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler` with `replicas` from `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, image from values, args including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, security contexts, volumes for config + emptyDir.\n97: \n98: ## RBAC rules (exact apiGroups / resources / verbs)\n99: \n100: ### ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n101: \n102: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n103: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n104: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n105: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n106: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n107: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n108: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n109: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n110: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n111: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n112: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n113: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n114: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n115: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n116: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n117: \n118: ### Role `router` (optional)\n119: \n120: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n121: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n122: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n123: \n124: ### ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` (when enabled)\n125: \n126: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n127: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n128: | `apiextensions.k8s.io` | `customresourcedefinitions` | `create,get,list,watch,delete` |\n129: | `\"\"` | `events` | `create,list,watch,update,patch` |\n130: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch,patch,delete` |\n131: | `\"\"` | `pods/status` | `update` |\n132: | `\"\"` | `pods/binding` | `create` |\n133: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumeclaims` | `list,watch,update` |\n134: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumes` | `list,watch,update` |\n135: | `\"\"` | `namespaces,services,replicationcontrollers` | `list,watch,get` |\n136: | `\"\"` | `resourcequotas` | `list,watch` |\n137: | `\"\"` | `nodes` | `get,list,watch,update,patch` |\n138: | `storage.k8s.io` | `storageclasses,csinodes,csidrivers,csistoragecapacities,volumeattachments` | `list,watch` |\n139: | `policy` | `poddisruptionbudgets` | `list,watch` |\n140: | `scheduling.k8s.io` | `priorityclasses` | `get,list,watch` |\n141: | `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io`, `scheduling.volcano.sh` | `podgroups` | `list,watch,update` |\n142: | `\"\"` | `configmaps` | `get,list,watch,create,delete,update` |\n143: | `apps` | `daemonsets,replicasets,statefulsets` | `list,watch,get` |\n144: | `coordination.k8s.io` | `leases` | `get,create,update,watch` |\n145: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch` |\n146: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims/status` | `update` |\n147: | `resource.k8s.io` | `deviceclasses,resourceslices` | `get,list,watch,create` |\n148: | `shard.volcano.sh` | `nodeshards` | `list,watch,get,update` |\n149: \n150: ## CRD definitions shipped (`manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n151: \n152: | File | CRD `metadata.name` | group | versions | scope | Notes |\n153: |------|---------------------|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n154: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` (served+storage); printer column Age | `Namespaced` | `openAPIV3Schema` includes root fields `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`, `status`. **spec.required**: `maxSessionDuration`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`. **Key spec fields**: `maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`); `sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`); `targetPort` (array of port objects: required `port`, `protocol` enum HTTP/HTTPS, optional `name`, `pathPrefix`); `podTemplate` (annotations, labels, nested `spec` = full PodSpec-shaped schema). **status**: conditions, etc. Annotation `controller-gen.kubebuilder.io/version: v0.17.2` |\n155: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `Namespaced` | **spec** includes `authMode` enum `picod|none` default `picod`; `maxSessionDuration` default `8h`; `sessionTimeout` default `15m`; `ports` (same TargetPort shape as above); `template` (image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.); optional `warmPoolSize` int32. **spec.required**: `template`. **status**: `conditions`, `ready`; subresource `status`. Same controller-gen version annotation |\n156: \n157: ## Dockerfiles\n158: \n159: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (workloadmanager)\n160: \n161: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n162: |-------|------|---------|\n163: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | `WORKDIR /workspace`; copy `go.mod`/`go.sum`; `go mod download`; copy `cmd/`, `pkg/`; build `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` with BuildKit cache mounts |\n164: | runtime | `alpine:3.19` | `apk add ca-certificates`; `WORKDIR /app`; copy binary; `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`; `USER apiserver`; `EXPOSE 8080`; `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`; `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]` |\n165: \n166: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux`, `TARGETARCH` (implicit platform).\n167: \n168: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n169: \n170: Same pattern as workloadmanager builder, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/`; output binary `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router`; runtime user `router` UID 1000; `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`.\n171: \n172: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n173: \n174: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n175: |-------|------|---------|\n176: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` | `WORKDIR /app`; copy mod files; download; `COPY . .`; build `picod` from `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n177: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` | `apt-get install -y python3`; `WORKDIR /root/`; copy binary; **runs as root** (comment: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions); `ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]` |\n178: \n179: ## Makefile — variables (key)\n180: \n181: | Variable | Default / definition |\n182: |----------|----------------------|\n183: | `HUB` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` |\n184: | `TAG` | `latest` |\n185: | `PROJECT_DIR` | directory of Makefile |\n186: | `GOBIN` | from `go env` |\n187: | `CONTAINER_TOOL` | `docker` |\n188: | `SHELL` | `/usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail` |\n189: | `LOCALBIN` | `$(shell pwd)/bin` |\n190: | `CONTROLLER_GEN` | `$(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen` |\n191: | `GOLANGCI_LINT` | `$(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint` |\n192: | `CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION` | `v0.17.2` |\n193: | `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `v1.64.1` |\n194: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n195: | `ROUTER_IMAGE` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n196: | `PICOD_IMAGE` | `picod:latest` |\n197: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `\"\"` |\n198: | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` |\n199: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_REPO` | `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox.git` |\n200: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `main` (Makefile comment; E2E script overrides — see CI design) |\n201: \n202: ## Makefile — targets\n203: \n204: | Target | Depends / notes |\n205: |--------|-----------------|\n206: | `all` | → `build` |\n207: | `help` | awk help from `##` comments |\n208: | `gen-crd` | `controller-gen`; `crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` → `manifests/charts/base/crds` |\n209: | `generate` | `controller-gen object` + `gen-crd` + `go mod tidy` |\n210: | `gen-client` | `bash hack/update-codegen.sh`; `go mod tidy` |\n211: | `gen-all` | `generate` + `gen-client` |\n212: | `gen-check` | `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code` |\n213: | `build` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` |\n214: | `build-agentd` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` |\n215: | `build-router` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` |\n216: | `build-all` | `build` + `build-agentd` + `build-router` |\n217: | `run` | `go run ./cmd/workload-manager/main.go --port=8080 --ssh-username=sandbox --ssh-port=22` |\n218: | `run-local` | same with `--kubeconfig=${HOME}/.kube/config` |\n219: | `run-router` | `go run ./cmd/router/main.go --port=8080 --debug` |\n220: | `clean` | `rm -rf bin/` and root binaries |\n221: | `deps` | `go mod download`; `go mod tidy` |\n222: | `update-deps` | `go get -u ./...`; `go mod tidy` |\n223: | `test` | `go test -v ./...` |\n224: | `fmt` | `go fmt ./...` |\n225: | `vet` | `go vet ./...` |\n226: | `lint` | `$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...` |\n227: | `gen-copyright` | `hack/update-copyright.sh` |\n228: | `install` | `build` + `sudo cp bin/workloadmanager /usr/local/bin/` |\n229: | `docker-build` | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n230: | `docker-buildx` | buildx linux/amd64,arm64 |\n231: | `docker-buildx-push` | requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY`; buildx `--push` |\n232: | `docker-push` | tag+push workloadmanager |\n233: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE)` |\n234: | `docker-build-router` / `docker-buildx-router` / `docker-buildx-push-router` / `docker-push-router` / `kind-load-router` | same pattern for router image |\n235: | `docker-build-picod` / `docker-buildx-picod` / `docker-buildx-push-picod` / `docker-push-picod` | same for picod |\n236: | `controller-gen` / `golangci-lint` | download via `go-install-tool` macro |\n237: | `e2e` | `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n238: | `e2e-clean` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n239: | `build-python-sdk` | copy `LICENSE` to `sdk-python`, `python3 -m build` in `sdk-python`, remove copied LICENSE |\n240: \n241: ## hack/ scripts\n242: \n243: | File | Purpose |\n244: |------|---------|\n245: | `hack/update-codegen.sh` | Runs `k8s.io/code-generator` **v0.34.1**: sources `kube_codegen.sh`, calls `kube::codegen::gen_client --with-watch --output-dir client-go --output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go --boilerplate hack/boilerplate.go.txt --one-input-api runtime/v1alpha1` on `pkg/apis`; post-processes lister files with `sed` to append `.GroupResource()` for codeinterpreter/agentruntime resources |\n246: | `hack/update-copyright.sh` | Prepends Apache/Volcano boilerplate to `*.go` and `*.py` under git root (excluding vendor/venv) if missing “Copyright The Volcano Authors”; uses `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` / `hack/boilerplate.py.txt`; requires `sponge` (moreutils) |\n247: | `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` | Go file header template |\n248: | `hack/boilerplate.py.txt` | Python file header template |\n249: \n250: ## Helm / E2E reference command (from `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n251: \n252: Illustrative install used in E2E:\n253: \n254: ```bash\n255: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n256:   --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n257:   --create-namespace \\\n258:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n259:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n260:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n261:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n262:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"},{\"name\":\"JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE\",\"value\":\"agentcube\"}]' \\\n263:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n264:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n265:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n266:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n267:   --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n268:   --wait\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Images are expected to be loaded into Kind with local names `workloadmanager:latest`, `agentcube-router:latest`, `picod:latest` after `make docker-build` variants.\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Design\n\nSource tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n\n## Chart.yaml\n\n| Field | Value |\n|--------|--------|\n| `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n| `name` | `agentcube` |\n| `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n| `version` | `0.1.0` |\n| `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n\n## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n\n| Path | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n| `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/deployment/design.md","time":{"start":1775874944117,"end":1775874944123}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775874944209,"sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","part":{"id":"prt_d7a652cc0001WIpYu5Usyyk6HP","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a651e2d0019nYYpU339630uK","sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":18395,"input":18255,"output":106,"reasoning":34,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.00526952}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775874946151,"sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","part":{"id":"prt_d7a653464001CxCvU54qijgrLZ","messageID":"msg_d7a652ce7001Zn4FvPHdidmprY","sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875031450,"sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6548a3001L9jFGRfe2Lf243","messageID":"msg_d7a652ce7001Zn4FvPHdidmprY","sessionID":"ses_2859c41dbffeQlJr2ka4W01qkP","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_499d7399212842179027984b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Purpose\n\nProvide three multi-stage Dockerfiles to build production-ready container images for AgentCube's core binaries: Workload Manager, Router, and picod. Each Dockerfile separates the Go compilation stage from the minimal runtime stage, reducing final image size, eliminating build-time dependencies from production images, and running binaries as non-root users where security permits. The images are built via Makefile targets and loaded into Kind for E2E testing or pushed to `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` for production deployment.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **`docker/Dockerfile`** | Workload Manager multi-stage build (golang:1.24.9-alpine → alpine:3.19) |\n| **`docker/Dockerfile.router`** | Router multi-stage build (golang:1.24.9-alpine → alpine:3.19) |\n| **`docker/Dockerfile.picod`** | picod multi-stage build (golang:1.24.4 → ubuntu:24.04) |\n| **Makefile targets** | `docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` and their buildx/push/kind-load variants |\n| **Build context** | Repository root (all three Dockerfiles use `.` as context) |\n| **Multi-arch support** | `docker-buildx` targets for linux/amd64 and linux/arm64 |\n| **Non-root runtime** | `apiserver` (UID 1000) for workloadmanager, `router` (UID 1000) for router |\n| **Security hardening** | `CGO_ENABLED=0`, `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"`, minimal base images, ca-certificates only |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` (separate AR, Python-based example)\n- CI/CD pipeline integration for automated image push (covered by ci-cd spec)\n- Helm chart image tag management (handled by `values.yaml`)\n- Docker Compose orchestration (not required for AgentCube deployment model)\n- Image scanning / SBOM generation\n- Runtime user for picod (runs as root by design — requires `chattr` on pubkey and sandbox permissions)\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `docker/Dockerfile` | Workload Manager: 2-stage build, outputs `workloadmanager` binary |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Router: 2-stage build, outputs `agentcube-router` binary |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | picod: 2-stage build, outputs `picod` binary |\n\n### `docker/Dockerfile` (Workload Manager)\n\n```dockerfile\n# Build stage\nFROM golang:1.24.9-alpine AS builder\nWORKDIR /workspace\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\nCOPY cmd/ cmd/\nCOPY pkg/ pkg/\nRUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n    CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} \\\n    go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n\n# Runtime stage\nFROM alpine:3.19\nRUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY --from=builder /workspace/workloadmanager /app/workloadmanager\nRUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver\nUSER apiserver\nEXPOSE 8080\nENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]\nCMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n```\n\n| Stage | Detail |\n|-------|--------|\n| builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine`; copies only `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `cmd/`, `pkg/`; BuildKit cache mount for `go build`; `CGO_ENABLED=0` for static binary; `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"` strips debug symbols |\n| runtime | `alpine:3.19`; only `ca-certificates` installed; binary copied from builder; non-root user `apiserver` UID 1000; exposes 8080 |\n\nBuild args: `TARGETOS=linux` (default), `TARGETARCH` (set by buildx platform).\n\n### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n\n```dockerfile\n# Build stage\nFROM golang:1.24.9-alpine AS builder\nWORKDIR /workspace\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\nCOPY cmd/ cmd/\nCOPY pkg/ pkg/\nCOPY client-go/ client-go/\nRUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n    CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} \\\n    go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o agentcube-router ./cmd/router\n\n# Runtime stage\nFROM alpine:3.19\nRUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY --from=builder /workspace/agentcube-router /app/agentcube-router\nRUN adduser -D -u 1000 router\nUSER router\nEXPOSE 8080\nENTRYPOINT [\"/app/agentcube-router\"]\nCMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]\n```\n\n| Stage | Detail |\n|-------|--------|\n| builder | Same as workloadmanager, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/` (generated Kubernetes clientset); outputs `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router` |\n| runtime | `alpine:3.19`; non-root user `router` UID 1000; default CMD includes `--debug` flag |\n\n### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n\n```dockerfile\n# Build stage\nFROM golang:1.24.4 AS builder\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\nCOPY . .\nRUN CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o picod ./cmd/picod\n\n# Runtime stage\nFROM ubuntu:24.04\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y python3\nWORKDIR /root/\nCOPY --from=builder /app/picod ./picod\n# Runs as root: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions require elevated privileges\nENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]\n```\n\n| Stage | Detail |\n|-------|--------|\n| builder | `golang:1.24.4` (note: different version from control plane); `COPY . .` copies entire repo (picod is a separate module at repo root); no BuildKit cache mount |\n| runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` (not Alpine — requires `python3` for sandbox subprocess execution); runs as root (comment documents rationale) |\n\n### Makefile Docker targets\n\n| Target | Command |\n|--------|---------|\n| `docker-build` | `$(CONTAINER_TOOL) build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n| `docker-build-router` | `$(CONTAINER_TOOL) build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t $(ROUTER_IMAGE) .` |\n| `docker-build-picod` | `$(CONTAINER_TOOL) build -f docker/Dockerfile.picod -t $(PICOD_IMAGE) .` |\n| `docker-buildx` | `docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(HUB)/workloadmanager:$(TAG) .` |\n| `docker-buildx-router` | Same pattern for router image |\n| `docker-buildx-picod` | Same pattern for picod image |\n| `docker-buildx-push` | As above with `--push`; requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY` set |\n| `docker-buildx-push-router` | Same for router |\n| `docker-buildx-push-picod` | Same for picod |\n| `docker-push` | `docker tag` + `docker push` for workloadmanager |\n| `docker-push-router` | Same for router |\n| `docker-push-picod` | Same for picod |\n| `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)` |\n| `kind-load-router` | Same for router |\n\n### Image characteristics\n\n| Image | Builder base | Runtime base | Binary | User | Port |\n|-------|-------------|--------------|--------|------|------|\n| workloadmanager | golang:1.24.9-alpine | alpine:3.19 | `workloadmanager` | apiserver (1000) | 8080 |\n| agentcube-router | golang:1.24.9-alpine | alpine:3.19 | `agentcube-router` | router (1000) | 8080 |\n| picod | golang:1.24.4 | ubuntu:24.04 | `picod` | root | N/A |\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `docker/Dockerfile` | ~18 |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.router` | ~20 |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | ~14 |\n\n### Files modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `Makefile` | Add `docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` targets and variants |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Usage |\n|------------|-------|\n| Docker / Podman | Container image build runtime (`CONTAINER_TOOL` variable) |\n| BuildKit | Cache mount support in builder stage (`--mount=type=cache`) |\n| docker buildx | Multi-arch cross-compilation (`--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64`) |\n| Kind | E2E image loading (`kind load docker-image`) |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | References image `repository:tag` for each component |\n| `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` | Expects images built and loaded into Kind cluster |\n| GitHub Actions CI | Calls `docker-buildx-push` targets for automated publishing |\n| Helm install command | Uses image names from `values.yaml` overrides |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n**None**: These are new files. No existing Dockerfiles or build processes are replaced.\n\n### Performance characteristics\n\n- **Build cache efficiency**: `go.mod`/`go.sum` copied before source code — dependency download cached independently of code changes\n- **BuildKit cache mount**: `/root/.cache/go-build` persisted across builds, reducing compile time for unchanged packages\n- **Final image size**: Alpine runtime (~5-10 MB) vs full golang image (~300+ MB); estimated 95%+ size reduction\n- **Multi-arch**: Single `docker-buildx` invocation produces both amd64 and arm64 manifests\n\n### Edge cases handled\n\n1. **Cross-platform build**: `GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH}` build args set by buildx for correct target architecture\n2. **Static binary**: `CGO_ENABLED=0` ensures no dynamic library dependencies on Alpine runtime\n3. **Symbol stripping**: `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"` removes debug info and symbol table, further reducing binary size\n4. **picod root requirement**: Documented in Dockerfile comment; cannot run as non-root due to `chattr` and sandbox permission requirements\n5. **Go version divergence**: picod uses golang:1.24.4 (not 1.24.9) — pinned to picod module's tested version\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Single-stage Dockerfiles\n\n**Approach**: Use full `golang` image as runtime, compile and run in the same stage.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Final image size ~300-500 MB vs ~10 MB for multi-stage (30-50x larger)\n- Exposes build toolchain (compiler, linker, source code) in production image — security risk\n- Longer pull times for deployment, especially in air-gapped or low-bandwidth environments\n- Violates container best practice of minimal runtime images\n\n### 2. Distroless base images (gcr.io/distroless/static)\n\n**Approach**: Use Google's distroless images as runtime base instead of Alpine.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Distroless `static` has no package manager — cannot install `ca-certificates` or `python3` (required by picod)\n- Distroless `base` (Debian-based) is larger than Alpine (~20 MB vs ~5 MB)\n- picod requires `python3` at runtime — distroless does not provide it without custom extension\n- Alpine provides sufficient minimalism with `apk` for the few required packages\n- Workload Manager and Router only need `ca-certificates` — Alpine handles this with negligible overhead\n\n### 3. Shared builder image for all three binaries\n\n**Approach**: Single Dockerfile with multiple builder stages and multiple runtime stages, producing all three binaries from one build.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Violates single-responsibility: one Dockerfile per deployable artifact is standard practice\n- Forces rebuild of all binaries when only one changes (no independent caching)\n- picod requires different Go version (1.24.4) and full repo copy (`COPY . .`) — incompatible with control-plane builder\n- Helm chart expects separate image repositories (`workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`, `picod`)\n- CI/CD pipelines build and push images independently per component\n\n### 4. Binary-only COPY from pre-built artifacts\n\n**Approach**: CI builds Go binaries on host/runner, Dockerfile only copies pre-compiled binary into runtime image.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Loses reproducibility: Docker build no longer self-contained — depends on external build environment\n- Cross-compilation complexity shifts from Docker build args to CI matrix configuration\n- No build cache benefit — every CI run recompiles from scratch\n- Developer local builds (`make docker-build`) would require matching Go toolchain on host\n- Multi-stage Dockerfile provides identical output with better encapsulation\n\n### 5. Ubuntu runtime for all images (uniformity)\n\n**Approach**: Use `ubuntu:24.04` as runtime base for all three images instead of mixing Alpine and Ubuntu.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Workload Manager and Router are pure Go static binaries — Ubuntu's glibc, coreutils, and package manager add ~70 MB of unnecessary attack surface\n- picod requires Ubuntu for `python3` — this is a genuine dependency, not a preference\n- Alpine's musl libc is compatible with `CGO_ENABLED=0` static binaries (no libc needed at runtime)\n- Security scanning would flag Ubuntu images for more CVEs due to larger package footprint\n- The marginal benefit of base image uniformity does not outweigh the security and size costs","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"proposal.md","time":{"start":1775875031405,"end":1775875031448}}}}
